NOTE:  We do not accept resumes without an official City of Tempe
application.  There are three ways to receive an application for an open
position:

*       You can down load applications (and supplements - if required) at
this address:   http://www.tempe.gov/hrrec/jobs.htm   Look for the title of
the position and download the appropriate documents corresponding to the
position.

*       You can drop by the Human Resources office at 20 East Sixth Street,
Tempe, AZ 85281 and pick up an application (and supplement - if required).

*       We can mail you an application to your address. Please e-mail me
your mailing address if you want us to send an application to you.



DETENTION OFFICER
(Police Department - Support Services)

OPENING DATE:  January 17, 2003
CLOSING DATE: Subject to closing when the needs of the City are met.  First
review of applications will be January 31, 2003- position may close at that
time.
HOURLY STARTING RATE:  $15.603
MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS:  Requires one year of experience as a Corrections or
Detention Officer, plus completion of the twelfth grade, or G.E.D.
supplemented by course work in criminal justice or related field.  Proof of
Certification as a Corrections / Detention Officer from a federal, state or
county training facility is also required and must accompany the candidates
application.  An AUTOMATIC AND DISCRETIONARY DISQUALIFIERS must be signed
and returned with your application.
ADDITIONAL REQUIREMENTS:  This position also requires possession of, or the
ability to obtain, an appropriate Arizona driver's license.  Referred
applicants will receive a polygraph exam and background investigation.
Successful completion of probationary period is contingent upon passing a
FBI background investigation.
Recruitment Code: 1385


Committed to Equal Opportunity and Reasonable Accommodation

